What does fails-to-deliver mean? Failure to deliver (FTD) refers to a situation where one party in a trading contract (whether it's shares, futures, options, or forward contracts) doesn't deliver on their obligation. Such failures occur when a buyer (the party with a long position) doesn't have enough money to take delivery and pay for the transaction at settlement. -investopedia.com Where is this data from? This data is downloaded twice a month directly from the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The data is publically available from the SEC here. How often is the data updated?
